<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ja/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/</link><description>Recent content in OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>ja</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ja/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ja/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/3-zpages/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ja/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/3-zpages/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zpages"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;zPages&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#zpages" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector/blob/main/extension/zpagesextension/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;zPages&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 は、外部エクスポーターに代わるインプロセスの手段です。有効にすると、バックグラウンドでトレースとメトリクスの情報を収集・集約し、リクエストに応じて Web ページでデータを提供します。zPages は、Collector が期待通りに動作していることを確認するための非常に有用な診断機能です。&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>